# Server (NestJS)

## kebab-case вЂ” always (non-negotiable)

**Every** hand-written file under `server/` uses **kebab-case** filenames. This is the project standard вЂ” no exceptions for new or renamed files.

| вњ… Correct | вќЊ Wrong |
|-----------|---------|
| `auth-controller.ts` | `auth.controller.ts`, `AuthController.ts` |
| `app-module.ts` | `app.module.ts`, `AppModule.ts` |
| `response-transform-interceptor.ts` | `responseTransformInterceptor.ts` |
| `http-exception-filter.ts` | `http-exception.filter.ts`, `httpException.filter.ts` |

- **Folders**: kebab-case (`modules/auth/`, `common/pipes/`).
- **Classes**: PascalCase in code (`AuthController`) вЂ” only the **file** is kebab-case.
- **Imports**: paths must match kebab-case filenames (`from './auth-service'`, `from 'src/common/pipes/zod-validation-pipe'`).

If Nest CLI scaffolds PascalCase or dot-notation files, **rename to kebab-case** before committing.

---

Follow the **existing** structure exactly. Do not introduce alternate patterns (class-validator-only DTOs, logic in controllers, or non-kebab-case filenames).

